cks).  I ussually fill an earth pet with all the junk, and he lasts me the whole time im on.  (Only gear to write home about, burntwood staff, and have muzzle now.)<br>
<br>
helpful hints:<br>
<br>
1.  If there is a curate near by kill him first.<br>
<br>
2.  If your getting adds in the tunnels, your spending to much time in them.  Get to a room and camp it.  Some have wonders that come and go, but most all rooms have a safe spot to med and not worry about the wonderers.  <br>
<br>
3.  Don't touch Barduck.<br>
<br>
4. Curates = clerics<br>
    Defilers = necros <br>
    Oracles = Shammies<br>
    Warriors = warriors<br>
    healers = lower lvl clerics<br>
    gnolls = lower lvl warriors<br>
    Barduck = one bad pos that will tear through a mid-lvl group in no time.<br>
<br>
5.  Don't let em do the walk of death, most of the time you will be in trouble.  Large cavern you can allow this somewhat.<br>
<br>
6.  Safest solo spot, is 2 rights from entrance.  have lev. up you will fall down a fake floor.  This will put you in a tunnel that has perfect pathing for fearing mobs, or mages to sit and med while grabbing the pulls just ahead.<br>
<br>
7.  Warriors which are the majority of the spawns don't see invis.  unless they have been hanging out with a caster.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
